Title: 2ZR-FXE (ENGINE CONTROL): THROTTLE BODY: REMOVAL; 2016 - 2022 MY Prius [11/2015 -        ]

REMOVAL

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during throttle body assembly removal/installation are shown below.

Necessary Procedures After Parts Removed/Installed/Replaced

Replaced Part or Performed Procedure

Necessary Procedure

Effect/Inoperative Function when Necessary Procedure not Performed

Link

  • Replacement of throttle body assembly
  • Cleaning the deposits from the throttle body assembly

Inspection After Repair

  • Poor idle, etc.
  • Engine start function, etc.

CAUTION:

Do not remove the reserve tank cap, air release valve (w/ air release valve) or radiator drain cock plug while the engine and radiator assembly are still hot. Pressurized, hot engine coolant and steam may be released and cause serious burns.

PROCEDURE

1. REMOVE REAR MOTOR UNDER COVER LH

Click here

2. DRAIN ENGINE COOLANT (for Engine)

Click here

3. REMOVE NO. 1 ENGINE COVER SUB-ASSEMBLY

Click here

4. REMOVE AIR CLEANER CAP SUB-ASSEMBLY

(a) Disconnect the mass air flow meter sub-assembly connector.

(b) Disconnect the wire harness clamp.

(c) Disengage the 2 clamps.

*a

Clamp

*b

Guide

(d) Disengage the 2 guides and remove the air cleaner cap sub-assembly from the air cleaner case sub-assembly.

(e) Loosen the hose clamp and remove the air cleaner cap sub-assembly from the air cleaner hose assembly.

5. REMOVE AIR CLEANER HOSE ASSEMBLY

(a) Slide the clip and disconnect the No. 2 ventilation hose from the cylinder head cover sub-assembly.

(b) Loosen the hose clamp and remove the air cleaner hose assembly from the throttle body assembly.

6. REMOVE THROTTLE BODY ASSEMBLY

(a) Disconnect the throttle body assembly connector.

*A

w/ Stud Bolt

*B

w/o Stud Bolt

*1

Water By-pass Hose

*2

No. 2 Water By-pass Hose

(b) Slide the 2 clips and disconnect the water by-pass hose and No. 2 water by-pass hose from the throttle body assembly.

(c) w/ Stud Bolt:

(1) Remove the 2 bolts, 2 nuts and throttle body assembly from the intake manifold.

*A

w/ Stud Bolt

*B

w/o Stud Bolt

(d) w/o Stud Bolt:

(1) Remove the 4 bolts and throttle body assembly from the intake manifold.

7. REMOVE THROTTLE BODY GASKET

(a) Remove the throttle body gasket from the intake manifold.
